column1: #text=My girlfriend 's birthday was coming up and instead of my usual buying a cake from the grocery store every year , I thought I would unleash my inner Paula Dean and bake her a cake .
#text=I went to the store and bought an easy yellow cake mix , some eggs , butter and icing .
#text=I decided to do it this way because when it comes to me and cooking I am not the best so easy was the way to go .
#text=I went home and got out a mixing bowl and added the cake box mix , two eggs , a stick of butter and a cup of water .
#text=I mixed it up and then poured the batter into a large baking pan and licked the beaters .
#text=I baked it at 350 for 15 minutes and it came out a perfect golden brown .
#text=After letting it cool for a bit I put on the chocolate icing that I bought and needless to say the cake was a huge hit and she was very impressed with my baking skills .
